  "body": "# Feature\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nNew state management has one deficiency. During migration, if the archived slot happens to have a skip block, then that archived slot will not have any state saved. In the following example, assume 32 slots configured as archived slot interval:\r\n ```\r\nINFO state-gen: Saved archived point during state migration archiveIndex=1 root=0xA slot=32\r\nslot 64 is skipped\r\nINFO state-gen: Saved archived point during state migration archiveIndex=3 root=0xC slot=96\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat will be ideal:\r\n ```\r\nINFO state-gen: Saved archived point during state migration archiveIndex=1 root=0xA slot=32\r\nINFO state-gen: Saved archived point during state migration archiveIndex=2 root=0xA slot=64\r\nINFO state-gen: Saved archived point during state migration archiveIndex=3 root=0xC slot=96\r\n```\r\n",
